The uStore will notify the service requester/notification subscriber when service becomes available:
  • new services in the defined area of interest becomes available
  • the ticket request has been fulfilled (completed)
  • the ticket request receives a responder that estimates a delivery date and price

For every service will exist feedback mechanism that includes reviews, ratings & rankings, questions/answers, bugs, satisfaction, proposal of new feature etc. Anyone will be allowed to write a feedback. All involved people (that uploaded the service or configured to be notified) will receive a notification about the feedback. Service providers may create personalized questionnaires to check satisfaction of users through uStore and send it to all users of their services.

uStore will provide a Quality Assurance process - AAL software services will be tested with the Conformance Tools developed within Task 3.3 - AAL services will be confirmed manually by administrators or trusted reviewers
uStore will allow all users to write a feedback about the uStore itself

uStore will serve AAL User Community - Feedback for every service provider/developer/group can be given by users - Feedback for every service can be given by users Other users will see the public feedback and can have a discussion.

The uStore will allow any registered user to create a ticket - request for new service/ability/feature.
The ticket will hold information about service category, requester, date/time, service details (text, picture, voice recording).
It will be possible to add requester contact information (to elaborate on details).
A receipt will be sent to the requester on request submission.
